Sine Square

The secret prism cartridge


---

Overview

Sine Square is both:

a flagship title

and a hidden cartridge class


It begins as a minimal interaction:

> a square falls, you move it left and right, and something about sound changes.



It ends as:

> a host-shaped, recursive, wave-based pinball instrument that feeds its own development back into the system.



Most cartridges move forward.

Sine Square bends the system back onto itself.


---

Core Law

Sine Square operates on a single principle:

> It reflects and refracts.



Reflection → sends developmental pressure back into Orange Home

Refraction → reshapes the signal flowing through it into structured musical form


This makes Sine Square not just a game, but a recursive development engine for the entire system.


---

Why it exists

Home is built on a few core ideas:

systems should emerge from interaction

input is proposal, not just command

meaning and form are relational

tools and games are not separate

the host is not fixed


Sine Square proves something deeper:

> The beginning can be changed by what comes after it.



After interacting with Sine Square, Orange Home itself becomes different:

it interprets input differently

it condenses rules differently

it “expects” different kinds of play


No two hosts remain identical after contact.


---

The experience arc

Phase 1 — Proof

a square falls

you move left/right

basic signal interaction

almost nothing else


This is intentional.

It demonstrates the relationship without showing its depth.


---

Phase 2 — Condensation

collisions begin to matter

simple surfaces appear

signal begins to stabilize into pattern


You are no longer observing.
You are shaping.


---

Phase 3 — Table Emergence

The system condenses into pinball logic:

bumpers

walls

ramps

gates

traps


Not as decoration.
As musical operators.


---

Phase 4 — Instrument

triggers control flippers and pressure surfaces

movement becomes phrase-shaping

collisions become rhythm and tone

structure emerges from interaction


You are no longer playing a game.

> You are playing a table-shaped instrument.




---

Phase 5 — Recursion

your play feeds back into Orange Home

the host changes

future sessions begin differently


Sine Square becomes part of the machine’s memory.


---

The Pinball Framework

Pinball is not aesthetic here.
It is structural.

It provides:

indirect control with high expressive depth

local interactions producing global structure

timing-based emergence

reflection as a primary mechanic


Each table element carries dual meaning:

Element	Mechanical Role	Musical Role

Bumper	bounce	accent / emphasis
Flipper	control	articulation
Ramp	path	phrase extension
Gate	constraint	timing filter
Trap	hold	tension / suspension
Drain	reset	phrase ending / transformation



---

Body Evolution

The square is only the beginning.

Over time, bodies may emerge:

Ball → smooth flow, continuous phrasing

Square → sharp edges, discontinuity

Triangle → directional instability, cuts

Hexagon → complex repeating cycles

Symbolic forms (e.g. “7”, smiley, glyphs) → host-conditioned behavior


Each body is:

> not just a shape
but a physics-poetic system



Different bodies produce different music.


---

Input Philosophy

Control is intentionally limited at the start:

left/right movement only


This enforces:

indirect influence

pressure-based interaction

emergence through constraint


Later:

triggers control flippers, gates, and timing surfaces

input becomes expressive rather than directive



---

Reflection (Host Feedback)

This is the defining feature.

Sine Square sends information back to Orange Home:

not as data

not as unlocks

but as development pressure


This can change:

how input is interpreted

what systems emerge first

how tightly rules condense

what kinds of structures feel “natural”


The host becomes biased by experience.


---

Refraction (Signal Transformation)

While reflection goes backward, refraction moves forward.

Sine Square reshapes flow into:

rhythm

tone

structure

phrase


It can:

tighten or loosen signal

concentrate or diffuse pressure

create waves from motion

produce musical coherence from collision



---

Recording and Output

When combined with capture cartridges:

Sine Square can produce:

songs

performance artifacts

reusable system states

instrument presets (host-dependent)


Important:

> These are not static outputs.
They carry the history of interaction.




---

Why it is hidden

Sine Square is not introduced explicitly.

It is discovered.

This matters because:

it reframes how the system is understood

it reveals recursion as a core law

it rewards deep engagement


The correct experience is:

> “This small thing I ignored…
is actually changing everything.”




---

Who it is for

Sine Square is not for:

passive players

immediate reward seekers

users expecting clear boundaries between tools and games


It is for:

player-creators

system thinkers

people who enjoy indirect control

people who notice when systems change under them



---

Respect Barrier

If approached as:

